  "text": "The present study was designed to consider the role of distraction by phone conversations, texting, and listening to music on college students' pedestrian safety. We examined pedestrian behavior within an interactive, semi-immersive virtual pedestrian environment previously validated to represent real-life pedestrian behavior [CITATION_1] . This permitted us to test potentially dangerous pedestrian behavior in an ethical manner. The study was conducted using a between-subjects design whereby participants were randomly assigned to talk on the phone, text, or listen to music while crossing the virtual street. A no-distraction control group was also included.",
